Englandâ€™s Raheem Sterling and Bukayo Saka found the net for a second and third time in the 43rd and 45th minutes to increase Englandâ€™s lead to 3-0. The scoring didnâ€™t stop there as Bukayo Saka would score again in the 62nd minute. Iran showed some life and notched their first goal of the World Cup in the 65th minute via Mehdi Taremi.
